definition.value: A carbon dioxide saturation is a ratio of the partial pressure of carbon dioxide to the barometric pressure, expressed as a percentage. [Allotrope]
An oxygen saturation is a ratio of the partial pressure of oxygen to the barometric pressure, expressed as a percentage. [Allotrope]
pCO2 is a partial pressure that quantifies the partial pressure of carbon dioxide dissolved in solution. [Allotrope]
pO2 is a partial pressure that quantifies the partial pressure of oxygen gas dissolved in solution. [Allotrope]
A PCR aggregate document is a document that aggregates PCR documents. [Allotrope]
A PCR document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some PCR experiment. [Allotrope]
A total partition count is a count of the number of partitions detected during a measurement. [Allotrope]

A fluorescence intensity threshold setting is a data processing setting that sets the fluorescence threshold value for objects within a measurement to be considered positive for a reporter. [Allotrope]
A positive partition count is a count of the number of partitions classified as being positive relative to a threshold. [Allotrope]
A negative partition count is a count of the number of partitions classified as being negative relative to a threshold. [Allotrope]
A reference DNA copy number is a PCR result specifying the DNA copy number of a reference gene or endogenous control within a PCR experiment. [Allotrope]
An image count setting is a control setting that specifies the number of images to be collected in the acquisition process. [Allotrope]
A sampling depth setting is a control setting that specifies the focal depth of a probing signal. [Allotrope]
A probe volume is the volume of a sample actively being measured by a detector or probe. [Allotrope]

A number concentration (datum) is a quantification facet that quantifies a concentration defined as the number of entities of a constituent in a mixture divided by the volume of the mixture. [Allotrope]
A spectrophotometry aggregate document is a document that aggregates spectrophotometry documents. [Allotrope]
A spectrophotometry document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some spectrophotometry run. [Allotrope]
A cell path length setting is a control setting that specifies some cell path length. [Allotrope]
An attenuation coefficient setting is a control setting that specifies some attenuation coefficient. [Allotrope]
A multi analyte profiling aggregate document is a document that aggregates multi analyte profiling documents. [Allotrope]
A multi analyte profiling document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some multi analyte profiling run. [Allotrope]

label.value: minimum assay bead count threshold setting

definition.value: A minimum assay bead count threshold setting is a control setting that specifies the threshold value for assay bead counts to be reported. [Allotrope]
An assay bead count is a count of the number of assay beads. [Allotrope]
An assay bead identifier is an identifier that identifies some assay bead or beads. [Allotrope]
A stress aggregate document is a document that is about a collection of stress documents. [Allotrope]
A stress document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a stress. [Allotrope]
A mass attenuation coefficient setting is a control setting that specifies some mass attenuation coefficient. [Allotrope]
A molar attenuation coefficient setting is a control setting that specifies some molar attenuation coefficient. [Allotrope]
A mass attenuation coefficient is an attenuation coefficient where the concentration is a mass concentration. [Allotrope]
An error aggregate document is a document that aggregates error documents. [Allotrope]
An error document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some error. [Allotrope]
An error feature is a facet that defines the feature with the role of a description or classification of a property, characteristic or facet of some data with the role of error. [Allotrope]
A temperature monitoring aggregate document is a document that aggregates temperature monitoring documents. [Allotrope]
A temperature monitoring document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a temperature measurement. [Allotrope]
A stirring aggregate document is a document that aggregates stirring documents. [Allotrope]
A stirring document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a stirring process. [Allotrope]
A pressure monitoring aggregate document is a document that aggregates pressure monitoring documents. [Allotrope]
A pressure monitoring document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a pressure measurement. [Allotrope]
A pH monitoring aggregate document is a document that aggregates pH monitoring documents. [Allotrope]
A pH monitoring document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a pH measurement. [Allotrope]
An absorption profile is a profile that quantifies the optical spectrometry absorbance of a material entity over time. [Allotrope]
An absorption profile data cube is a data cube that represents an absorption profile. [Allotrope]
A fluorescence emission profile is a profile that quantifies the fluorescence emission of a material entity over time. [Allotrope]
A fluorescence emission profile data cube is a data cube that represents a fluorescence emission profile. [Allotrope]

label.value: solution-state nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy aggregate document

definition.value: A solution-state nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy aggregate document is a document that aggregates solution-state nuclear magnetic resonance documents. [Allotrope]

label.value: solution-state nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy document

definition.value: A solution-state nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a solution-state nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy run. [Allotrope]
An ASM file is a file that conforms to the Allotrope Simple Model specification. [Allotrope]
An ASM file identifier is an identifier that identifies some ASM file. [Allotrope]

A nuclear magnetic resonance frequency is the frequency at which NMR active nuclei absorb electromagnetic radiation. It is characteristic of the isotope and is proportional to the strength of the magnetic field of the instrument. [Wikipedia]
A nuclear magnetic resonance solvent type is a classification datum that classifies the solvent used in a solution-state nuclear magnetic resonance assay. [Allotrope]
